title: Sights and Sounds: Kentucky beats EKU, 34-27 in OT
text:
LEXINGTON ,Ky. (WYMT) -- Kentucky improved to 4-1 on the year with an overtime win over Eastern Kentucky (2-2) Saturday night inside Commonwealth Stadium. 
The Wildcats won 34-27 thanks to Dorian Baker's go-ahead touchdown with under a minute to go in regulation to send it to overtime, and his catch in OT that ended up being the game-winner. 
Check out the video above for the sights and sounds of the game from the radio, TV and fan's perspective.
